
# Terraform EC2 Auto Deploy

This project automates the deployment of an Amazon EC2 instance using Terraform. Upon provisioning, the instance runs a Bash script that installs and configures Nginx.

## 📌 Tech Stack
- AWS (EC2, VPC, Security Groups)
- Terraform
- Bash Scripting
- GitHub Actions (CI/CD)

## 📁 Project Structure

terraform/ │   └── main.tf
│   └── variables.tf
│   └── outputs.tf
scripts/ │   └── setup-nginx.sh
docs/ │   └── architecture.png

## ⚙️ How to Use

1. Clone the repo:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Tommy813-lab/Terraform-EC2-Auto-Deploy.git

2. Customize variables in terraform.tfvars


3. Initialize and apply:

terraform init
terraform apply


4. SSH into the instance:

ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@<public-ip>



🧱 Architecture



🔐 Security

.pem file not committed (add to .gitignore)

Least-privilege IAM roles

Open ports restricted to your IP


📸 Output Example



